        "type": "message",
        "text": "Exercise:\n• Refactor orders controller to use authenticate_user\n• Add admin boolean column to User table with default value of false\n• Use a `before_action :authenticate_admin` to prohibit non-admin users from creating, updating, and deleting products. (You’ll need to create the `authenticate_admin` method in the application_controller).\nBonus:\n• If you run `rails test`, your products controller tests will fail for create\/update\/destroy.\n    ◦ This is because they now require an admin’s jwt in the headers!\n    ◦ See if you can update your tests (you can look at the orders controller tests to see how to make a jwt and include it in each header)",
